00:23:14.400 --> 00:23:17.460
which over time fragments into a number

00:23:17.460 --> 00:23:21.360
of different entities,
of which one is Moscow.

00:23:21.360 --> 00:23:23.520
Of which one is Moscow.

00:23:23.520 --> 00:23:25.620
Now, how is Moscow different?

00:23:25.620 --> 00:23:27.600
Moscow is different in religion.

00:23:27.600 --> 00:23:29.520
It's not Pagan as the Mongols are,

00:23:29.520 --> 00:23:31.830
to use the term of abuse
that the Christians use.

00:23:31.830 --> 00:23:34.650
And Moscow doesn't convert to Islam.

00:23:34.650 --> 00:23:35.640
This is important too.

00:23:35.640 --> 00:23:38.340
The rest of these
entities convert to Islam.

00:23:38.340 --> 00:23:43.340
So, but Moscow doesn't,
Moscow is Orthodox.

00:23:43.890 --> 00:23:46.170
Moscow's Orthodox, but it's Orthodox

00:23:46.170 --> 00:23:48.060
in an interesting way, right?

00:23:48.060 --> 00:23:51.840
It's Orthodox in a place,
mark this for the future.

00:23:51.840 --> 00:23:53.121
It's Orthodox in a place

00:23:53.121 --> 00:23:56.070
where there's no other
way of being Christian.

00:23:56.070 --> 00:23:57.540
This is really important, I mean,

00:23:57.540 --> 00:23:59.190
I think right down to the present moment.

00:23:59.190 --> 00:24:00.660
There's no other way of being Christian.

00:24:00.660 --> 00:24:03.030
If you're Christian,
you're Orthodox, that's it.

00:24:03.030 --> 00:24:07.080
Whereas west of this, in Kyiv
and in the rest of Europe,

00:24:07.080 --> 00:24:09.660
there are going to be lots of
other ways of being Christian.

00:24:09.660 --> 00:24:11.730
And even if you are Orthodox,

00:24:11.730 --> 00:24:14.880
in what's now Ukraine,
Belarus, Poland, Lithuania,

00:24:14.880 --> 00:24:16.740
you're going to be in
a series of encounters

00:24:16.740 --> 00:24:19.950
with other sorts of Christians
over the next few centuries.

00:24:19.950 --> 00:24:21.750
In Moscow, this is not true.

00:24:21.750 --> 00:24:25.230
Orthodoxy is Christianity,
Christianity is Orthodoxy.

00:24:25.230 --> 00:24:28.560
And this is all, and related
to this, also to mark,

00:24:28.560 --> 00:24:30.450
there isn't any theology.

00:24:30.450 --> 00:24:34.740
There isn't any disputation
about religion in Moscow.

00:24:34.740 --> 00:24:37.110
In points further west
there is going to be,

00:24:37.110 --> 00:24:39.270
the Orthodox are going to take part

00:24:39.270 --> 00:24:40.770
in all of the interesting conversations

00:24:40.770 --> 00:24:43.170
around Reformation,
Counter-Reformation, all of that.

00:24:43.170 --> 00:24:46.530
That's not going to be happening
in Moscow until much later,

00:24:46.530 --> 00:24:50.250
when Moscow and Kyiv come into
contact for the first time,

00:24:50.250 --> 00:24:51.960
which is not for centuries.

00:24:51.960 --> 00:24:53.790
It's not for centuries,
it's not in this lecture,

00:24:53.790 --> 00:24:56.160
it's in the 17th century, okay.

00:24:56.160 --> 00:24:59.640
So we're in Mongol Rus'.

00:24:59.640 --> 00:25:02.580
Mongol Rus' is the northeast.

00:25:02.580 --> 00:25:06.573
It's the district which I
mentioned last time, Suzdal.

00:25:09.840 --> 00:25:13.170
And then Suzdal, surrounding territories,

00:25:13.170 --> 00:25:17.457
the northeast of what had been Rus'.

00:25:18.705 --> 00:25:23.705
And the way that the political
system is set up by this,

00:25:25.440 --> 00:25:29.340
is set up in this Northeastern
Rus', this Mongol Rus',

00:25:29.340 --> 00:25:31.890
is really a kind of fresh start,

00:25:31.890 --> 00:25:34.800
in the sense that the Mongols
have come and destroyed.

00:25:34.800 --> 00:25:37.290
Okay, good, that's true for everyone.

00:25:37.290 --> 00:25:40.320
Then there's the Black
Death, it's a bit of a mess.

00:25:40.320 --> 00:25:42.543
There's really no one around to write.

00:25:43.590 --> 00:25:47.520
And in addition to that, a new principle

00:25:47.520 --> 00:25:49.680
of political succession is set up.

00:25:49.680 --> 00:25:52.350
The principle of political
succession in the old Rus',

00:25:52.350 --> 00:25:55.680
the one based in Kyiv
was admittedly very messy

00:25:55.680 --> 00:25:57.720
and to the point of incomprehensibility,

00:25:57.720 --> 00:26:00.810
but it had something to do
with the ruler and his sons.

00:26:00.810 --> 00:26:02.820
That's about as much as we can say.

00:26:02.820 --> 00:26:04.740
And that's by the way,
not so unusual in Europe.

00:26:04.740 --> 00:26:06.300
This whole idea that
it was the eldest son,

00:26:06.300 --> 00:26:07.290
and it was all very simple.

00:26:07.290 --> 00:26:09.420
That usually covers over a whole bunch

00:26:09.420 --> 00:26:13.530
of illegitimacy and
bloodshed, but you know, okay.

00:26:13.530 --> 00:26:16.680
So illegitimacy and
bloodshed gets a lot of nods.

00:26:16.680 --> 00:26:18.330
I just wanna record that for the camera.

00:26:18.330 --> 00:26:21.689
All right, so focus.

00:26:21.689 --> 00:26:26.400
So in Northeastern Rus',
in and around Suzdal,

00:26:26.400 --> 00:26:29.043
there's a new succession
principle which is,

00:26:29.910 --> 00:26:34.910
how well can you collect
taxes for the Mongol overlord?

00:26:35.760 --> 00:26:37.460
That's the new principle of power.

00:26:38.550 --> 00:26:41.760
So the Mongols accept that
there's something called Rus'.

00:26:41.760 --> 00:26:43.890
They have no trouble with that,

00:26:43.890 --> 00:26:46.710
but who is the Grand Prince of Rus'?

00:26:46.710 --> 00:26:49.110
The Grand Prince of Rus' is

00:26:49.110 --> 00:26:51.420
the person who can collect the tribute.

00:26:51.420 --> 00:26:53.850
So that is a new principle of rule.

00:26:53.850 --> 00:26:57.900
That is new compared to Kyiv obviously,

00:26:57.900 --> 00:26:59.190
where if you were in Kyiv,

00:26:59.190 --> 00:27:00.810
you were the one taking
the tribute, right?

00:27:00.810 --> 00:27:04.200
And by the way, this is a
really fundamental thing

00:27:04.200 --> 00:27:05.790
about political power.

00:27:05.790 --> 00:27:08.370
If you want to figure out
who is actually in charge,

00:27:08.370 --> 00:27:10.680
who is paying tribute to whom?

00:27:10.680 --> 00:27:13.740
Because everyone says,
"I'm the king and the tsar,

00:27:13.740 --> 00:27:16.119
and all the galaxies," and so on, right?

00:27:16.119 --> 00:27:17.640
That's very easy.

00:27:17.640 --> 00:27:20.340
Having stationary, okay, they
didn't have stationary yet,

00:27:20.340 --> 00:27:24.510
but having a list of
titles is very easy, right?

00:27:24.510 --> 00:27:27.900
But what really matters is,
are you paying the tribute,

00:27:27.900 --> 00:27:30.630
or is someone paying the tribute to you?

00:27:30.630 --> 00:27:34.410
So the rulers of Muscovy
had titles, right?

00:27:34.410 --> 00:27:37.440
They were the Grand Princes of Moscow,

00:27:37.440 --> 00:27:40.514
which sounds great and
certainly had its pluses.

00:27:40.514 --> 00:27:44.790
But they were paying
tribute to the Mongols,

00:27:44.790 --> 00:27:47.810
and they were the Grand Princes of Moscow

00:27:47.810 --> 00:27:50.970
because they could pay
tribute to the Mongols.

00:27:50.970 --> 00:27:54.420
The Mongols chose the man who
could collect the tribute.

00:27:54.420 --> 00:27:57.630
And so that's a different
principle of succession.

00:27:57.630 --> 00:28:01.290
The people who ran Mongol
Rus' were princes of,

00:28:01.290 --> 00:28:04.020
they were princes who were
descended from the old Rus'.

00:28:04.020 --> 00:28:06.390
Not in any particular distinction,

00:28:06.390 --> 00:28:08.820
but they were of the blood,

00:28:08.820 --> 00:28:10.530
but they were only the
Grand Princes of Rus'

00:28:10.530 --> 00:28:12.870
because they were the ones
who could collect the taxes.

00:28:12.870 --> 00:28:15.300
And then the other way
that this is a fresh start

00:28:15.300 --> 00:28:20.300
is that the whole system
is based in a new city,

00:28:22.050 --> 00:28:23.370
which is Moscow.

00:28:23.370 --> 00:28:26.700
So Moscow existed as some
kind of fort or something

00:28:26.700 --> 00:28:30.540
in the 12th century, but
Moscow had no princely line.

00:28:30.540 --> 00:28:32.700
Moscow is not a district in old Rus'.

00:28:32.700 --> 00:28:35.310
Nobody goes to Moscow
to rule anything, right?

00:28:35.310 --> 00:28:39.840
It's not one of these districts
Suzdal or like Chernihiv,

00:28:39.840 --> 00:28:41.640
where you go and you rule.

00:28:41.640 --> 00:28:42.960
It's not a district at all.

00:28:42.960 --> 00:28:45.330
It's no place, it's nowhere.

00:28:45.330 --> 00:28:50.250
Moscow becomes a town,
becomes a meaningful place

00:28:50.250 --> 00:28:55.250
with a princely line after the
Mongol destruction of Kyiv,

00:28:55.860 --> 00:28:58.620
and because it's a Prince of Moscow

00:28:58.620 --> 00:29:01.260
who's able to collect the tribute.

00:29:01.260 --> 00:29:04.010
It was also, well, there's
also some marriage involved.

00:29:05.910 --> 00:29:10.770
In 1317, Yuri, who was a Prince of Moscow,

00:29:10.770 --> 00:29:14.883
married the sister of the Khan
of the Golden Horde, right?

00:29:15.810 --> 00:29:18.570
As one does, you know, in
situations like this, right?

00:29:18.570 --> 00:29:22.860
So he also marries into
power, and at that point,

00:29:22.860 --> 00:29:26.460
power passed durably from a more important

00:29:26.460 --> 00:29:29.430
bigger city called Tver to Moscow.

00:29:29.430 --> 00:29:31.140
And from that point, Moscow is gonna be

00:29:31.140 --> 00:29:35.370
the center of this entity.

00:29:35.370 --> 00:29:37.590
And it's gonna be the Princes of Moscow

00:29:37.590 --> 00:29:39.450
who eventually remember,
it takes them a while,

00:29:39.450 --> 00:29:40.627
but who eventually remember to say,

00:29:40.627 --> 00:29:44.070
"We are the rulers of all of Rus'."

00:29:44.070 --> 00:29:46.830
The first one, by the way
to, as far as we know,

00:29:46.830 --> 00:29:49.080
who says that he's the ruler of all Rus'

00:29:49.080 --> 00:29:53.997
was Vasily I, who ruled from 1389 to 1399.

00:29:53.997 --> 00:29:56.097
And the evidence we have is there's a coin

00:29:57.180 --> 00:30:02.070
where he appears, and he says,
"I am the ruler of all Rus'."

00:30:02.070 --> 00:30:04.597
On the other side of that coin, it says,

00:30:04.597 --> 00:30:07.890
"Long live Sultan Tokhtamysh",

00:30:07.890 --> 00:30:11.130
which reminds you of what the
actual political order is.

00:30:11.130 --> 00:30:13.590
He's the ruler of all of Rus', terrific.

00:30:13.590 --> 00:30:16.020
But what he means by all
of Rus' is the bit of Rus'

00:30:16.020 --> 00:30:19.290
that is under the control
of the Golden Horde, right?

00:30:19.290 --> 00:30:22.560
That's under the control of the Mongols.

00:30:22.560 --> 00:30:27.000
Now all of this, the Mongol
connection is very important

00:30:27.000 --> 00:30:30.360
because when the Mongol
connection is broken,

00:30:30.360 --> 00:30:33.483
the basic state form remains.

00:30:33.483 --> 00:30:36.360
There's no clear moment
in the history of Muscovy

00:30:36.360 --> 00:30:39.090
where you can say, "Okay,
the Mongols were here,

00:30:39.090 --> 00:30:40.320
they were doing everything,

00:30:40.320 --> 00:30:42.840
and then they got on their
little horses and left."

00:30:42.840 --> 00:30:44.910
That's not how it worked at all.

00:30:44.910 --> 00:30:46.920
The way that it worked was that

00:30:46.920 --> 00:30:49.120
somewhere in the middle
of the 15th century,

00:30:50.190 --> 00:30:52.110
Moscow stops paying tribute.

00:30:52.110 --> 00:30:53.850
But they don't change at that point,

00:30:53.850 --> 00:30:55.200
they just stop paying tribute.

00:30:55.200 --> 00:30:58.740
It's the same entity, okay?

00:30:58.740 --> 00:31:03.120
So have a state which is
in some way post Rus'.

00:31:03.120 --> 00:31:07.560
Religion, princely family,
language, all of that.

00:31:07.560 --> 00:31:10.050
But it's also in many ways a new start,

00:31:10.050 --> 00:31:12.120
a new start under the Mongols.

00:31:12.120 --> 00:31:17.120
So it's post post Rus', I would
say, and it's post Mongol.

00:31:18.240 --> 00:31:19.980
Let me say a word now about the system,

00:31:19.980 --> 00:31:23.340
because the system is
incredibly interesting.

00:31:23.340 --> 00:31:27.120
First of all, and to give
credit where credit is due,

00:31:27.120 --> 00:31:29.970
the Muscovites knew how to fight.

00:31:29.970 --> 00:31:31.740
And the reason they knew how to fight

00:31:31.740 --> 00:31:34.140
was that they fought with,

00:31:34.140 --> 00:31:36.660
and then eventually against the Mongols.

00:31:36.660 --> 00:31:38.970
So the Mongol cavalry techniques,

00:31:38.970 --> 00:31:41.070
which the Mongols brought
with them to Europe

00:31:41.070 --> 00:31:42.690
and which no one could withstand,

00:31:42.690 --> 00:31:45.480
were then learned by the
Muscovites, because of course,

00:31:45.480 --> 00:31:47.310
the Muscovites were
part of the same state.

00:31:47.310 --> 00:31:49.830
They were fighting on the same side.

00:31:49.830 --> 00:31:52.140
So they were very good at war.

00:31:52.140 --> 00:31:55.057
And the way that they set up
their armies in five parts

00:31:55.057 --> 00:31:56.283
has everything to do with the way

00:31:56.283 --> 00:31:59.160
that the Mongols set set up their armies.

00:31:59.160 --> 00:32:01.636
So that's very important to know.

00:32:01.636 --> 00:32:04.470
The Muscovites knew how to fight,

00:32:04.470 --> 00:32:06.990
that is part of their heritage.

00:32:06.990 --> 00:32:10.470
The heritage that they don't have is all

00:32:10.470 --> 00:32:13.920
the legal bureaucratic heritage of Kyiv,

00:32:13.920 --> 00:32:14.790
which we've talked about earlier.

00:32:14.790 --> 00:32:15.930
They're free and clear of that.

00:32:15.930 --> 00:32:18.690
For better or worse, they're
free and clear of that.

00:32:18.690 --> 00:32:21.295
It's rather the Lithuanians
who pick up that heritage,

00:32:21.295 --> 00:32:23.700
which means that the legal tradition

00:32:23.700 --> 00:32:27.090
in Mongol Rus' is very simple.

00:32:27.090 --> 00:32:30.813
It starts from the idea that
the tsar owns everything,

00:32:32.760 --> 00:32:33.593
which is convenient.

00:32:33.593 --> 00:32:36.630
I mean, it's very convenient
if you're the tsar.

00:32:36.630 --> 00:32:39.780
And okay, and when I say all this,

00:32:39.780 --> 00:32:43.553
don't overdo it, but do
record this and think about it

00:32:43.553 --> 00:32:46.320
when you're thinking about
the history of Russia,

00:32:46.320 --> 00:32:48.273
the centuries, as centuries pass.

00:32:49.290 --> 00:32:52.563
So all the property belongs
to the tsar, the ruler.

00:32:53.970 --> 00:32:55.320
You can't really own land.

00:32:55.320 --> 00:32:57.300
You can own land conditionally.

00:32:57.300 --> 00:32:59.489
If I'm the tsar, I'm gonna be the tsar,

00:32:59.489 --> 00:33:01.410
'cause I'm the one who's talking.

00:33:01.410 --> 00:33:02.640
You can own land conditionally

00:33:02.640 --> 00:33:05.670
until I say that you don't anymore, right?

00:33:05.670 --> 00:33:07.870
So land ownership can
be broken at any time.

00:33:08.910 --> 00:33:12.990
You own land practically, in exchange

00:33:12.990 --> 00:33:15.030
for service to me, the tsar.

00:33:15.030 --> 00:33:19.140
So everyone who owns land by definition

00:33:19.140 --> 00:33:20.400
is a servant of the tsar,

00:33:20.400 --> 00:33:22.980
and almost always that's military service.

00:33:22.980 --> 00:33:25.320
So this is the way the army is set up.

00:33:25.320 --> 00:33:27.720
You get to control land, but in return,

00:33:27.720 --> 00:33:29.493
you serve in the army.

00:33:30.480 --> 00:33:31.530
That is the fundamental deal.

00:33:31.530 --> 00:33:35.463
You control land in exchange
for military service,

00:33:36.300 --> 00:33:38.000
and I can break that at any point.

00:33:39.090 --> 00:33:41.100
So you're the fighting class,

00:33:41.100 --> 00:33:43.710
but you're not exactly a nobility

00:33:43.710 --> 00:33:46.350
in the sense of West European nobilities.

00:33:46.350 --> 00:33:48.960
There is no legal list,
there's no register,

00:33:48.960 --> 00:33:50.940
there's no patent of nobility.

00:33:50.940 --> 00:33:52.200
There's no beautiful piece of paper

00:33:52.200 --> 00:33:53.647
which you can produce and say,

00:33:53.647 --> 00:33:56.340
"I have a better Latin script
than you," or whatever.

00:33:56.340 --> 00:33:58.560
You're not really nobles in the sense

00:33:58.560 --> 00:34:00.750
of being a legal estate.

00:34:00.750 --> 00:34:04.080
You're really nobles it more
or less at my at my pleasure.

00:34:04.080 --> 00:34:05.580
So there aren't property rights,

00:34:05.580 --> 00:34:08.040
and there aren't really
feudal rights either.

00:34:08.040 --> 00:34:10.500
There's this deal, which
is a very effective deal.

00:34:10.500 --> 00:34:12.690
It works very well, a fighting class

00:34:12.690 --> 00:34:14.070
in exchange for control of land.

00:34:14.070 --> 00:34:16.380
And of course it works very well,

00:34:16.380 --> 00:34:19.170
so long as we're getting
more land all the time.

00:34:19.170 --> 00:34:20.970
And that's part of the
magic of the system.

00:34:20.970 --> 00:34:23.970
We are going to be getting
more land all the time

00:34:23.970 --> 00:34:25.631
for at least a couple of centuries.

00:34:25.631 --> 00:34:29.340
The state is going to grow spectacularly,

00:34:29.340 --> 00:34:31.080
first west into Europe,

00:34:31.080 --> 00:34:33.180
then south into formerly
Muslim territories,

00:34:33.180 --> 00:34:35.190
and then west all the
way to the Pacific Ocean

00:34:35.190 --> 00:34:37.320
in just a couple of centuries, okay.

00:34:37.320 --> 00:34:40.350
This is basically an
agrarian country though.

00:34:40.350 --> 00:34:45.350
So part of this system is serfdom.

00:34:45.420 --> 00:34:50.420
So you are off fighting wars,
but you have a land manager

00:34:50.850 --> 00:34:54.120
and you have serfs on your territory.

00:34:54.120 --> 00:34:57.060
The Russian peasants live in communes.

00:34:57.060 --> 00:34:59.010
The word for commune, I forgot
to write this down, sorry,

00:34:59.010 --> 00:35:00.870
is (speaking in Russian),
which is a very evocative

00:35:00.870 --> 00:35:03.450
Russian word, 'cause it
also means world and peace,

00:35:03.450 --> 00:35:05.820
which is practically a whole
universe of meaning, right?

00:35:05.820 --> 00:35:09.750
So commune, peace and
world, all the same word.

00:35:09.750 --> 00:35:12.420
The right that the
peasants had in the system,

00:35:12.420 --> 00:35:16.140
The one right, was to leave
and go somewhere else.

00:35:16.140 --> 00:35:17.730
So think about how this works.

00:35:17.730 --> 00:35:19.740
The peasants are in a commune.

00:35:19.740 --> 00:35:21.870
The commune is on the land of someone

00:35:21.870 --> 00:35:23.280
who's in this warrior class.

00:35:23.280 --> 00:35:24.480
The person who's in the warrior class

00:35:24.480 --> 00:35:26.310
is personally dependent upon the tsar.

00:35:26.310 --> 00:35:29.550
No way anywhere down in this hierarchy

00:35:29.550 --> 00:35:32.220
does anyone really have
any kind of formal rights.

00:35:32.220 --> 00:35:34.440
The right that the
peasants have is to leave,

00:35:34.440 --> 00:35:38.400
and the story of serfdom is
that that right is taken away.

00:35:38.400 --> 00:35:43.400
Beginning from 1497 through
let's say through 1649,

00:35:45.900 --> 00:35:48.870
all of these rights are
completely taken away.

00:35:48.870 --> 00:35:51.600
So in 1497, I'm not gonna
tell the whole story,

00:35:51.600 --> 00:35:56.600
but in 1497, you're right as peasants,

00:35:56.610 --> 00:35:57.443
okay, I'll be the peasant.

00:35:57.443 --> 00:36:01.620
My right as a peasant to leave
is limited to one day a year.

00:36:01.620 --> 00:36:02.970
Okay, that's a restriction.

