And that's not just a matter of territory,

00:48:44.460 --> 00:48:46.470
it's also a matter of human variety.

00:48:46.470 --> 00:48:49.710
There are roughly 500
groups in this territory,

00:48:49.710 --> 00:48:52.110
speaking roughly 120 languages.

00:48:52.110 --> 00:48:54.120
And many of these groups still exist,

00:48:54.120 --> 00:48:55.650
and you can read about them in the news

00:48:55.650 --> 00:48:58.920
as they're being mobilized
to fight in Ukraine.

00:48:58.920 --> 00:49:00.870
But it's also, as I've tried to stress,

00:49:00.870 --> 00:49:03.810
it's globalization,
because Russia is trading

00:49:03.810 --> 00:49:06.240
the Atlantic and the
Pacific at the same time.

00:49:06.240 --> 00:49:09.450
And finally, this is the very
last sentence, with China.

00:49:09.450 --> 00:49:12.780
So one of the limits, one of
the few limits that Russia,

00:49:12.780 --> 00:49:16.200
that Moscow reaches is with the Chinese.

00:49:16.200 --> 00:49:19.830
They reach, they sign a
peace treaty with China

00:49:19.830 --> 00:49:24.660
in 1689 in Nerchinsk, which
establishes the border

00:49:24.660 --> 00:49:26.490
between Muscovy and China.

00:49:26.490 --> 00:49:29.730
But more importantly, it
establishes terms of trade

00:49:29.730 --> 00:49:32.460
between Muscovy and China
so that all those furs

00:49:32.460 --> 00:49:35.760
can be traded to China for luxury goods.

00:49:35.760 --> 00:49:39.510
So the route to China, which the English

00:49:39.510 --> 00:49:41.910
were trying to discover,
eventually does take place,

00:49:41.910 --> 00:49:45.960
but by way of land rather
than by way of sea.

00:49:45.960 --> 00:49:49.605
So this is the origins of Muscovite power.

00:49:49.605 --> 00:49:54.605
A new system, an enormous
amount of new territory,

00:49:54.930 --> 00:49:59.010
and the success of
centralization in all of this.

00:49:59.010 --> 00:50:01.890
What this has to do with
all of Rus', of course,

00:50:01.890 --> 00:50:03.630
you know, is very fuzzy.

00:50:03.630 --> 00:50:05.790
If I've gotten anything
across, I hope it's this,

00:50:05.790 --> 00:50:08.490
that Rus' has many successors,

00:50:08.490 --> 00:50:10.440
and we wouldn't want deny the connection

00:50:10.440 --> 00:50:13.140
between Rus' to Galicia-Volhynia,
or to Lithuania,

00:50:13.140 --> 00:50:16.770
or at the state that's founded in Moscow.

00:50:16.770 --> 00:50:21.270
But Moscow also has very much
to do with the Mongol period,

00:50:21.270 --> 00:50:24.270
which lasts for so very much
longer there than elsewhere.

00:50:24.270 --> 00:50:25.920
And it has very much to do with the fact

00:50:25.920 --> 00:50:28.950
that its first moves when
it comes into existence,

00:50:28.950 --> 00:50:33.420
are territorial expansion to
Europe, but mostly into Asia.

00:50:33.420 --> 00:50:34.953
Okay, thank you very much.

